Asta Funding, Inc. (NASDAQ:ASFI) Sees Significantly Higher Trading Volume 












































 Finance DailyDaily markets, commodities, personal finance and economic newsAsta Funding, Inc. (NASDAQ:ASFI) Sees Significantly Higher Trading Volume
July 17, 2017 By Ted Blackburn Tweet
        Advertisement



Trading was heavy with 14K shares changing hands by the end of trading on Friday.  Overall, volume was up 152.47% over the stocks normal daily volume. 
 Traders are a little more bearish on shares of Asta Funding, Inc. lately if you look at the change in short interest.  The firm had a rise in short interest between June 15, 2017 and May 31, 2017 of 43.60%.  Short interest grew 9,405 over that timeframe.  With short interest at 30,976 and short average daily volume at 10,751, days to cover is 2.9 and the short interest percentage is 0.00% as of May 31. 
 Here are some other firms who have updated their holdings.   As of the end of the quarter Tower Research Capital LLC (trc) had acquired  a total of 1,279 shares growing its stake by 31,975.0%. The value of the total investment in Asta Funding, Inc. increased from $0 to $10,000 increasing 0.0% quarter over quarter. Royal Bank Of Canada trimmed its investment by shedding 52,503 shares a decrease of 88.2% as of 03/31/2017. Royal Bank Of Canada controls 6,997 shares valued at $57,000. The total value of its holdings decreased 90.2%.        Advertisement






 As of quarter end Deutsche Bank Ag had bought 238 shares growing its position 247.9%. The value of the investment in (ASFI) went from $0 to $2,000 a change of $2,000 quarter to quarter. Dimensional Fund Advisors Lp downsized its holdings by selling 675,275 shares a decrease of 88.1% from 12/31/2016 to 03/31/2017. Dimensional Fund Advisors Lp currently owns 91,568 shares with a value of $751,000. The value of the position overall is down by 90.0%.
 The company is trading up since yesterday’s close of $7.  Company chares are trading at $7.15 slightly below the 50 day moving average of $7.36 and marginally under the 200 day moving average of $8.64.  The 50 day moving average moved down $-0.21 and the 200 day average went down by -17.27%. 
 The P/E ratio is 125.44 and the market value is 46.92M. 
 Asta Funding, Inc., launched on August 2, 1995, operates in the financial services industry. The Company is primarily engaged in the businesses of acquiring, managing, servicing and recovering on portfolios of consumer receivables. The Company operates through four segments: Consumer Receivables, Personal Injury Claims, Structured Settlements and GAR Disability Advocates. The Consumer receivables segment is involved in the business of purchasing, managing for its own account and servicing distressed consumer receivables, including charged off receivables, semi-performing receivables and performing receivables. The Personal injury claims segment includes the operations of its subsidiary, Pegasus Funding, LLC (Pegasus). The Structured settlements segment includes the operations of CBC Settlement Funding, LLC (CBC). The GAR Disability Advocates segment includes the operations of GAR Disability Advocates, LLC (GAR Disability Advocates)..
